headline: Baker Hughes (BKR) Is Up 5.7% After Record IET Backlog And New Energy Transition Deals - Has The Bull Case Changed?
summary: In late January 2026, Baker Hughes reported fourth-quarter 2025 earnings that topped analyst expectations and highlighted record orders and backlog from its Industrial & Energy Technology arm, while also announcing expanded roles in low-carbon ammonia and long-duration energy storage projects. By deepening its partnership with Hydrostor on advanced compressed air energy storage and securing key roles in Wabash Valley Resources’ low-carbon ammonia plant, Baker Hughes is further embedding its...
